decks.notes: This deck focuses on efficiently ramping up mana through land tutoring and interaction with Amulet of Vigor to quickly cast Primeval Titan and other powerful creatures. The deck utilizes various lands and spells to create a combo engine that can generate a lot of mana and overwhelm the opponent with large creatures. The goal is to set up a board state where Primeval Titan can search for key lands and quickly close out the game with powerful follow-up plays.

This deck focuses on using Jeskai Ascendancy to create a powerful combo with Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student. By utilizing various artifacts and creatures, the deck aims to generate infinite mana and draw cards to eventually win the game. Cards like Mishra's Bauble and Mox Opal help to trigger Jeskai Ascendancy's abilities, while counterspells like Metallic Rebuke and removal spells like Repeal provide protection and control. The deck's strategy revolves around assembling the combo pieces and controlling the game until achieving victory.

This aggro deck focuses on disruptive elements that disrupt the opponent's gameplan while applying pressure through efficient creatures. The deck combines flicker effects with powerful creatures that protect themselves or provide additional value, creating a board state that can overwhelm opponents quickly. By utilizing synergies between creatures and spells, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's resources and keep them on the back foot until it can secure victory. Additionally, the mana base is optimized for consistent access to the deck's powerful spells and creatures.

The deck focuses on setting up a combo with Broodscale Bloodchief by ramping up mana with Eldrazi Temple and Urza's Saga, while controlling the board with Glaring Fleshraker and Malevolent Rumble. Cards like Kozilek's Command and Devourer of Destiny provide additional support and disruption. Blade of the Bloodchief helps pump up creatures, while Sowing Mycospawn can generate additional tokens. The deck also includes powerful Eldrazi like Emrakul, the Promised End for a big finish. Overall, the strategy revolves around assembling the combo pieces and overwhelming the opponent with a mix of control and aggression.

The deck focuses on using a combination of creatures and enchantments to disrupt the opponent's game plan while creating a board presence that can quickly overwhelm them. By utilizing cards like Ephemerate and Solitude for removal and protection, along with powerful enchantments like Starfield Shepherd and Witch Enchanter, the deck aims to control the game tempo and protect its key creatures. Meanwhile, cards like Ocelot Pride and Quantum Riddler provide additional threats and card advantage. With a mix of creature-based aggression and disruptive enchantments, the deck aims to outmaneuver and outvalue the opponent.

The deck focuses on assembling a powerful combo utilizing cards like Basking Broodscale, Malevolent Rumble, and Devourer of Destiny to generate immense value and overwhelm opponents quickly. By ramping up mana with Eldrazi Temple and Urza's Saga, the deck aims to establish a dominant board presence, supported by cards like Glaring Fleshraker and Emrakul, the Promised End. Additionally, the inclusion of cards like Kozilek's Command and Blade of the Bloodchief provides additional utility and synergy to the combo pieces, allowing for explosive turns and efficient resource management.

This deck focuses on assembling a variety of creatures with different abilities to create synergies and combos. By using cards like Chord of Calling to search for specific creatures, such as Yawgmoth, Thran Physician, and Marionette Apprentice, the deck can generate value and create powerful board states. The Toolbox aspect allows for flexibility in adapting to different situations, while also providing a variety of win conditions through cards like Blood Artist and Grist, the Hunger Tide. Overall, the deck aims to outvalue and overwhelm opponents through creature interaction and combo potential.

This deck focuses on exploiting the opponent's resources while disrupting their game plan with a mix of aggressive creatures and disruptive spells. The goal is to maintain control of the game by using cards like Teferi, Time Raveler and Prismatic Ending to disrupt the opponent's plays, while deploying threats like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd to apply pressure and close out the game quickly. The deck aims to outmaneuver the opponent by leveraging its flexibility and versatility in both offense and defense.

The main concept of this deck is to use a combination of Mill cards and control spells to quickly deplete the opponent's library, while also disrupting their game plan with cards like Archive Trap and Surgical Extraction. By constantly milling the opponent's cards and taking advantage of graveyard interaction, this deck aims to win the game by forcing the opponent to draw from an empty library or by simply overwhelming them with mill effects. The inclusion of cards like Drown in the Loch and Fatal Push provide additional control options to deal with threats that may interfere with the deck's strategy.

Utilize land ramp and mana acceleration to quickly assemble the Amulet Titan combo, utilizing Primeval Titan to search for key lands such as Gruul Turf and Simic Growth Chamber. Use Amulet of Vigor to untap lands and generate extra mana, enabling explosive plays with cards like Scapeshift and Malevolent Rumble to overwhelm the opponent with powerful land triggers and search effects. The combination of land recursion and tutoring effects allows for strategic flexibility and the ability to adapt to different board states, while also providing a strong win condition through Primeval Titan's attacking power.

The deck focuses on utilizing powerful combo pieces such as Goryo's Vengeance and Quantum Riddler to quickly reanimate big threats like Griselbrand and Atraxa, Grand Unifier. The deck also includes various instant speed interaction like Thoughtseize, Force of Negation, and Prismatic Ending to disrupt opponents' game plans. Additionally, cards like Ephemerate and Faithful Mending provide card advantage and flexibility to the strategy. The deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and overwhelm the opponent with powerful threats while disrupting their game plan.

This deck focuses on assembling the UrzaTron lands (Urza's Power Plant, Urza's Mine, Urza's Tower) to generate huge amounts of mana, enabling powerful plays such as casting All Is Dust or Ugin, the Eye of the Storms. It also features control elements like Karn, the Great Creator and Thought-Knot Seer to disrupt the opponent's strategy. Devourer of Destiny and Glaring Fleshraker provide additional threats to apply pressure on the opponent. The deck utilizes Eldrazi Temple and Mind Stone for ramp and card draw, creating a versatile and resilient Control archetype.

This deck focuses on quickly deploying an army of artifacts to overwhelm the opponent, using cards like Mishra's Bauble, Memnite, and Mox Opal to generate mana and card advantage. Emry, Lurker of the Loch provides value by recurring artifacts from the graveyard, while cards like Engineered Explosives and Metallic Rebuke offer disruption and protection. The main goal is to have a fast and aggressive start, utilizing the affinity mechanic to power out threats and control the board with efficient spells like Thoughtcast and Sink into Stupor.

This Aggro - Affinity deck focuses on quickly overwhelming the opponent with a mix of artifacts and creatures, ensuring a fast and aggressive playstyle. It utilizes cards like Mishra's Bauble and Mox Opal to ramp up mana production and enable explosive turns. The deck also includes removal options like Engineered Explosives and Tormod's Crypt to control the board and disrupt the opponent's strategy. With a combination of fast mana and powerful threats like Salvage Titan and Kappa Cannoneer, this deck aims to win the game before the opponent has a chance to stabilize.

The main concept of this deck is to create a disruptive and aggressive strategy by combining "Death and Taxes" elements with an aggro playstyle. It aims to control the board with cards like Thoughtseize and Teferi, Time Raveler while also applying pressure with creatures like Quantum Riddler and Overlord of the Balemurk. The deck uses efficient removal spells like Fatal Push to deal with threats and has a strong card advantage engine with Ephemerate and Witch Enchanter. The deck's versatile mana base allows for flexibility in casting spells and adapting to different matchups.

This deck focuses on using the UrzaTron lands to quickly ramp up to powerful Eldrazi creatures like Emrakul, the Promised End. It includes a mix of control elements like counterspells and removal, as well as artifact synergy with cards like Karn, the Great Creator. The goal is to establish a dominant board presence and overwhelm the opponent with huge threats while disrupting their game plan with spells like Disruptor Flute and Kozilek's Command. Overall, the deck aims to control the game and win with its massive Eldrazi creatures.
